Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.20,0:01:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,THE BATTLE IN THE WHITE GARDEN
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.88,0:01:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So you managed to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.76,0:01:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not entirely correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.38,0:01:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I died once.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.93,0:02:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But, I was given the Dragon Blood\Nthat flows in Master Baran's veins.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.60,0:02:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It resurrected me from the brink of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.77,0:02:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dragon Blood?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.77,0:02:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What he used to resurrect Popp\Nafter his life ended!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.65,0:02:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Baran shared his Dragon Blood\Nwith us three Dragon Masters,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.70,0:02:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and laid us down in the forest\Nnear the Fountain of Miracles.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.16,0:02:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But Dragon Blood doesn't guarantee\Nthe resurrection of all who drink it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.17,0:02:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Only in those with the willpower necessary\Nto crawl back from the brink of death{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.26,0:02:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}is this effect observed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.51,0:02:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was the only one of us three\Nwho made it back.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.19,0:02:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I see. So it was Popp's strong will\Nthat allowed him to resurrect.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.40,0:03:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I awakened from my long slumber\Nin my coffin just a few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.28,0:03:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I almost missed this final battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.37,0:03:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. If you hadn't saved me, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.62,0:03:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't recall ever saving you, Hyunckel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.84,0:03:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I merely disposed of an enemy in my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.38,0:03:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no interest in rescuing losers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.51,0:03:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.72,0:03:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I know how soft you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.52,0:03:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Those wounds must be from\Nprotecting that enemy there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.39,0:03:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,An action unfitting of a Warrior,\Na professional in combat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.44,0:03:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.61,0:03:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.44,0:03:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You may be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.07,0:03:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.32,0:03:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hyunckel!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.53,0:03:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,To coldly analyze a situation\Nand defeat enemies like a machine...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.71,0:03:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's what makes a Warrior,\Nthen it's something I can no longer do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.63,0:03:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm no longer worthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.21,0:04:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what happened,\NI couldn't abandon Hym!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.59,0:04:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears that leaving the fates of\NMaster Baran and Master Dino in your hands
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.68,0:04:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,was a mistake on my part.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.31,0:04:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking at you like that, I doubt\Nyou'll be of any use to Master Dino!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.94,0:04:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What do you think you're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.61,0:04:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This man is too pitiful to let live.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.45,0:04:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to finish him myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.81,0:04:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,L-Larhart...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.18,0:04:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The Warrior Hyunckel is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.02,0:04:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I just killed him right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.32,0:05:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, there is no reason why\NI shouldn't take the Dark Armour Spear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.75,0:05:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.96,0:05:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A corpse has no use for armour.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\3c&H1717E4&}Amudo!{\i0}{\3c&H00000000&}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.97,0:05:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell my friend. May you rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.85,0:05:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Larhart...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.77,0:05:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You were too kind\Nto continue fighting forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.40,0:05:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Dammit! That Darkling pisses me off!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.49,0:05:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.41,0:05:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That was his own brand of kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.49,0:05:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he was sent\Nto protect Dai in my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.54,0:06:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A savior that Baran sent from the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.71,0:06:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a savior?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.80,0:06:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,By passing judgment on me,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.88,0:06:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,he took on my will and duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.64,0:06:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We both watched each other die.\NWhat a strange twist of fate.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.02,0:06:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've done all I could.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.44,0:06:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I even managed to rescue Hym.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Maybe now... Maybe now\Nno one will scold me...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.57,0:06:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mas... ter.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.49,0:06:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but it's that sort of "We've got a\Nspecial bond" attitude that's annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.13,0:06:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to have to\Nkick his butt someday, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.42,0:06:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoops. But first, once we're healed,\NI need to settle things with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.59,0:06:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you listening, Hyunckel?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.72,0:07:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hyunckel, thank you for using your body\Nto protect Master Dino until now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.60,0:07:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You can leave the rest to me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.82,0:07:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For I am the sort of\Nbattle machine you spoke of.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.99,0:07:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.70,0:07:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that Hyunckel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.41,0:07:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You're from the Royal Guard!\NWhy are you here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.96,0:07:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hyunckel! What happened to Hyunckel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.34,0:07:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up. Keep it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.38,0:07:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He's finally getting the rest he deserves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.18,0:07:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably for the first time in his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.18,0:07:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,he can forget about\Nfighting and destinies...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.39,0:07:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and rest his weary body and soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.11,0:07:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... Hyunckel?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.95,0:08:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears they were wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.87,0:08:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The King's Orichalcum Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.29,0:08:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.25,0:08:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But of course they were.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.01,0:08:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Maximum was just a delusional blowhard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.88,0:08:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Maximum did not have King Ban's favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That fool didn't know hunting a mouse\Nfrom finishing off a wounded beast.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.64,0:08:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So who took care of the Orichalcum Army?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.44,0:08:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It must have been\Nthe ones not present, Hyunckel or Aban.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.61,0:08:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.91,0:08:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Master Aban!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.54,0:08:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It must have been my first student\Nwho took care of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.00,0:08:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You're late, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.67,0:08:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We were worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.97,0:08:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh come on! It's not just Master Aban!\NI'm here, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.73,0:09:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.02,0:09:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean. It's not like we weren't\Nworried about you, Princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.28,0:09:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.32,0:09:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're Aban.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.03,0:09:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. You went ahead\Ninto the Tower of Supremacy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.66,0:09:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! We've already scouted\Nmost of the structure ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.29,0:09:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And we took care of\Nmost of the Reaper's traps, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.00,0:09:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Using my special item!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.76,0:09:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?! M-Master,\Nyou don't need to show them...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.64,0:09:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hup!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.77,0:09:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,These Mieru Glasses\NI found in the Cave of Trials
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.73,0:09:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,enable me to see through any trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.03,0:10:00.57,DefaultLow,,0,0,0,,{\\i1}{\\3c&H1717E4&}HAKENDISUTORU{\\i0}{\\3c&H00000000&}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.04,0:10:05.58,DefaultLow,,0,0,0,,{\\i1}{\\3c&H1717E4&}ABAGAMU{\\i0}{\\3c&H00000000&}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.75,0:10:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Swish, swish, swish!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.08,0:10:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,With my Mieru Glasses and hammer,\NI crush traps with a swish, swish, swish!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.09,0:10:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So much for Master's cool image.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.01,0:10:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If he had just kept quiet...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Master's in some kind of mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.93,0:10:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He could never let\Nany lame bit go to waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.85,0:10:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we waste our time worrying about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.94,0:10:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,-Huh?\N-H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.15,0:10:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,-It looks like Mystban finds it funny.\N-That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.66,0:10:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand now. What a fascinating man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.54,0:10:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never encountered\Na human like you, Aban.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.21,0:10:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I've known about you ever\Nsince you defeated the Dark Lord Hadorra.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.55,0:11:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But to actually see you\Nis something else altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.01,0:11:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You act in such a way\Nto hide your overwhelming talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.56,0:11:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And that profound integrity\NI sense from within you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.98,0:11:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder your disciples\Ncontinue to look up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.07,0:11:24.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Princess Leona has filled me in on\Nwhat's happened these past three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.08,0:11:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The current Dark Commander Mystban
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.62,0:11:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is apparently the greatest, most powerful\Nbarrier in the fight against Ban.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.92,0:11:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems what I was told is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.71,0:11:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You would be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.42,0:11:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing as there's no word from Zaboera,\NI can only assume he's been defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.34,0:11:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The self-proclaimed\N"most powerful" king also fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.31,0:11:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the only one left who can\Nexterminate the nuisances in Ban Palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.31,0:11:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Mystban, alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.65,0:12:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All the other former Six Legion Commanders\Nhave been defeated!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.28,0:12:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it's almost over!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.11,0:12:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Six Legion Commanders?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.28,0:12:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.08,0:12:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The Six Legion Commanders.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.50,0:12:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That was just a little amusement\NKing Ban created on a whim.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.04,0:12:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He could have always wiped out\Nthe surface world with me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.30,0:12:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But King Ban didn't want to\Njust destroy the surface world.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.59,0:12:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,By creating legions that would\Ncompete to carry out that purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.56,0:12:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,he wanted to gain the ultimate army\Nthat would last into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.81,0:12:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why he welcomed Hadorra, the most\Npowerful being in the surface world,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.19,0:12:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and placed me under his command.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Baran and Hyunckel were chosen\Nfor their spirit and hatred of humans.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.91,0:12:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Crocodine, for his loyalty.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.08,0:12:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Flazzard and Zaboera,\Nfor their ambition and wisdom.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.42,0:12:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They were chosen for\Nthe potential King Ban saw in them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.80,0:13:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to create a powerful army,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.05,0:13:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the tension between such varying\Npersonalities is essential.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.26,0:13:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But you managed to shatter that plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.10,0:13:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an unfortunate turn of events,\Nbut ultimately meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.27,0:13:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The Dark Army was but a fleeting dream\Nof the last few decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.24,0:13:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Its loss doesn't hamper our goal\Nof wiping out the surface world at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.78,0:13:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I alone, have been here\Nfor thousands of years!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.95,0:13:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I alone, have protected King Ban!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.67,0:13:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.05,0:13:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's the most dangerous of all of them!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.30,0:13:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's like he's on a whole different level\Nfrom the others!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.06,0:13:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, come at me all at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.14,0:14:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I shall make this White Garden your grave!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.69,0:14:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out, Dai!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.19,0:14:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He has a hidden face! An unknown power!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.40,0:14:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.99,0:14:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We fight at full power!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.45,0:14:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I will fight that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.88,0:14:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,By "you," do you mean by yourself, Aban?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.06,0:14:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's crazy, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.69,0:14:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.35,0:14:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If we fight together...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.11,0:14:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Master...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.61,0:14:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you accept my challenge, Mystban?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.99,0:14:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.66,0:14:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.74,0:14:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I had forgotten about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.96,0:15:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He tends to be very vindictive.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.17,0:15:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows what he'll do\Nif I try to take his prey?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.47,0:15:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.18,0:15:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A scythe?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.35,0:15:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Kilban! Kilban got Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.43,0:15:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it was you, Kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.77,0:15:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The Reaper lives up to his reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.11,0:15:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.53,0:15:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Myst... sorry, but I leave\Nthe others to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.20,0:15:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I've barely even started!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.37,0:15:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.41,0:15:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.56,0:16:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.65,0:16:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.90,0:16:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The Reaper took him and vanished!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.62,0:16:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You have lost him again, Dai.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.62,0:16:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just once, but twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.83,0:16:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it feel to lose\Nyour master before your eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.00,0:16:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I imagine your heart must be overcome\Nwith frustration and loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.67,0:16:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You did this together!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.01,0:16:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You worked with the Reaper\Nto assassinate Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.89,0:16:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That wasn't an assassination.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.98,0:16:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's something much more interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.10,0:16:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.11,0:16:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A duel?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.44,0:16:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The scythe that attacked Aban\Nwasn't Kill's favorite Reaper Flute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.49,0:16:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a guide to drag Aban\Nto the place of their duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.03,0:17:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Aban wasn't killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.79,0:17:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's about to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.30,0:17:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Where...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.68,0:17:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.73,0:17:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.77,0:17:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It-It's not moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.49,0:17:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That thing isn't targeting me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.91,0:17:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this strange robot thing\Nwhat dragged me into this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.96,0:17:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Bingo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.67,0:17:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Kilban!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.58,0:17:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello Aban. Welcome to\Nthe field of my revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.13,0:17:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally, I'd prefer to immediately\Nrepay you for humiliating me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.63,0:18:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but I couldn't decide\Nwhich mask to wear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.39,0:18:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I really liked the last one,\Nso finding a similar one was quite a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.60,0:18:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.44,0:18:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I managed to find\Nthe perfect mask for the occasion!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.11,0:18:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A... A Mask of Anger!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.70,0:18:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, this mask\Nrepresents my emotional state.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.74,0:18:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No man has ever wounded my pride\Nand caused me such anger as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.00,0:18:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If anyone, that little Mage student\Nof yours was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.34,0:18:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But as his master, you annoy me even more!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.80,0:18:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,As promised, I'm going to kill you myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.47,0:18:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're going with your anger\Nand giving up the smug facade?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.23,0:18:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So? What sort of dirty trap\Nhave you prepared this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.74,0:18:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider that a left-hand glove.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.45,0:19:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This time there are no traps.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.99,0:19:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Fair and square,\NI challenge you to a duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.16,0:19:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A duel?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.29,0:19:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what this field is for.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.54,0:19:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Take a look at that robot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.79,0:19:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's part of my collection\Nfrom the Underworld, called a Judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.22,0:19:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Its scythe has the ability to\Ntear reality and drag a target here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.64,0:19:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How did the residents\Nof the Underworld use it you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.85,0:19:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They used it as a dueling machine against\Nthose they had a score to settle with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.32,0:19:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, as the name implies,\Nthe Judge serves as overseer,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.28,0:19:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,presiding over the duel\Nbetween the individuals trapped here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.24,0:19:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Here, isolated together\Nin this empty field,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.25,0:19:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}they fight and fight and fight\Nuntil one finally falls!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.71,0:19:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And in the end, the Judge\Npasses its judgment!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.88,0:20:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes the loser's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.09,0:20:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What a terrifying machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.09,0:20:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,A fitting thing for the Underworld\Nwhere conflict never ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.81,0:20:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it because I rather like the design,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.64,0:20:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but I never imagined\NI'd be using it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.32,0:20:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know\Nwhat can prove useful in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.28,0:20:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Aban, will you accept my challenge?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean "accept"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.08,0:20:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that I'm here\Nmeans I have no choice but to accept!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.00,0:20:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't talk about "fair and square."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.88,0:20:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the definition\Nof "trap," Kilban!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.92,0:20:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That attitude!\NI can assume you accept this duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.18,0:20:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we fight, Aban!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.56,0:20:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What?! Kilban's using a sword?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.02,0:20:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Aban versus Kilban. Battle start.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Kilban draws first blood.\N65 damage to Aban.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.18,0:21:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Care to make a wager, Dai?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.60,0:21:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Which of us will come back here alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.64,0:21:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously, I place my bet on Kilban.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.14,0:22:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tell me, where are you going all alone?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.14,0:22:17.77,On Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}nee hitoridake de doko e yukuno{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.65,0:22:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I gaze at you from behind\Nas you begin to walk away{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.65,0:22:28.32,On Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}arukidasu kimi no ushirosugata wo nagameru{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.32,0:22:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tell me, where are you going all alone?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.32,0:22:36.12,On Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}nee hitoridake de doko e yukuno{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.92,0:22:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We act tough and follow our hearts{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.92,0:22:45.34,On Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}massugu de tsuyogari na sonna bokura ga{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.51,0:22:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And we began this tale together{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.51,0:22:49.76,On Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}hajimeta monogatari{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.26,0:22:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Beyond the horizon something glimmers{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.26,0:22:56.06,On Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}chiheisen no mukou de kirameiteiru{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.23,0:23:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've been seeking something certain{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.23,0:23:02.44,On Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}tashika na mono sagashitsuzukete iruno{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.07,0:23:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the distant sky, dancing in the wind{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.07,0:23:09.28,On Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}haruka sora ni kaze ni nori matte{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.45,0:23:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The birds sing as though\Nilluminating the future{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.45,0:23:15.08,On Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}tobu tori wa naiteita mirai wo terasuyouni{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.24,0:23:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The promise that connects us\NThe adventure we share{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.24,0:23:20.87,On Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}bokura wo tsunagu yakusoku to\Nbokura de tsumugu bouken wo{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.04,0:23:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Again in this world{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.04,0:23:27.05,On Top,,0,0,0,,{\i1}mata kono sekai de{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.80,0:23:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Aban was dragged into\Nanother dimension by Kilban.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.31,0:23:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was the wrathful Kilban's way\Nof challenging him to a duel.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.44,0:23:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Dai and his friends are shaken\Nfrom losing Aban again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.03,0:23:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just as it seems\Nthat Mystban has broken their spirit,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.24,0:23:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a single Feather strikes\Nthe ground at their feet.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.07,0:23:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,DRAGON QUEST The Adventure of Dai{\i1},{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.41,0:23:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}"The Successor of Justice"{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.25,0:24:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The adventure continues!{\i0}
